# Possible Image-Level Threats

## 1. Steganography

### LSB (Least Significant Bit) Embedding
- Data hidden in the lowest bit of each colour channel (R, G, B, Alpha)
- Imperceptible to human eye — pixel value changes by ±1
- Detection: bit-plane correlation, chi-square analysis, LSB skew
- Mitigation: LSB extraction + ASCII text scanning (spatial engine)

### LSB-2 / Bit-1 Plane
- Data hidden in the second-least significant bit
- More robust than LSB-1, harder to detect statistically
- Detection: extract bit-1 plane and scan for text
- Mitigation: multi-plane extraction (spatial engine)

### Palette-Based Hiding
- In palette (P) mode images, pixel values are indices into a colour lookup table
- Attacker reorders palette entries so indices encode a message
- Pixel values don't change visually — only the palette order
- Detection: not currently implemented
- **Mitigation: sanitizer converts P mode to RGB, resolving palette to absolute colour values**

### Alpha Channel Hiding
- Data hidden in the alpha (transparency) channel
- Fully transparent or fully opaque pixels can have modified alpha LSB without visible effect
- Detection: extract alpha LSB plane
- Mitigation: RGBA→RGB conversion strips alpha (JPEG), or 8-bit RGBA normalisation

### Post-EOF Payloads
- Data appended after end-of-file markers (PNG IEND, JPEG EOI, GIF trailer)
- Image parsers ignore trailing data, but it survives sanitization that re-encodes via PIL
- Detection: scan raw bytes for data after known EOF signatures
- Mitigation: structural engine finds and reports post-EOF text

### Metadata Hiding
- Data embedded in EXIF fields (GPS coordinates, camera make/model, thumbnails)
- PNG text chunks (tEXt, zTXt, iTXt)
- Comment fields, ICC profiles, XMP metadata
- Detection: inspect metadata field contents and sizes
- Mitigation: metadata engine reports findings; sanitizer strips all metadata via re-encode

### Colour Depth Abuse
- 16-bit per channel images — LSB data in the lower 8 bits is invisible in standard 8-bit viewers
- The extra byte per channel doubles hiding capacity per pixel
- Detection: extract LSB from all 16 bits (spatial engine works on raw bytes)
- **Mitigation: sanitizer converts all images to 8-bit RGB/RGBA, discarding upper bit planes**

### Non-Standard Colour Modes
- CMYK, YCbCr, LAB, 32-bit float (F), 32-bit int (I) images
- Unusual channel layouts and bit depths bypass standard analysis tools
- Channel math can hide data that only appears after colour space conversion
- Detection: requires per-mode knowledge of pixel layout
- **Mitigation: sanitizer converts all non-RGB modes to 8-bit RGB**

### Compression-Based Hiding
- Data embedded in JPEG quantisation tables or DCT coefficients
- PNG compression level manipulation (zlib level affects output, not data)
- GIF LZW minimum code size alteration
- Detection: requires full decompression cycle analysis (not implemented)
- Mitigation: PIL re-encode re-compresses with standard settings

