## 3. Polyglot Files

### Dual-Format Polyglot
- File that is valid in two formats simultaneously (e.g., PNG + ZIP, GIF + JS)
- Passes magic-byte validation as an image but executes as script
- Detection: check for embedded magic signatures within file
- Mitigation: not currently implemented; sanitizer re-encode destructs non-image content

### Chunk Injection (PNG)
- Additional PNG chunks inserted between required chunks (IHDR → ... → IDAT → IEND)
- Unknown chunk types are silently ignored by most parsers
- Data can be hidden in chunk names, lengths, or payload
- Detection: inspect all chunk types in PNG structure (not implemented)
- Mitigation: PIL re-encode produces only essential chunks (IHDR, IDAT, IEND)

---

## 4. Signature / Extension Mismatch

### Magic Byte Mismatch
- File extension says .png but magic bytes indicate GIF or EXE
- Downstream parser may interpret file differently than validator expected
- Detection: compare extension-derived MIME to magic-byte MIME
- Mitigation: reject if magic bytes do not match extension

### No Extension or Double Extension
- `file` has no extension → parser defaults to unknown handler
- `image.png.exe` double extension bypasses extension-only filters
- Detection: check for multiple dots, require known extension
- Mitigation: reject if no extension or double extension detected

